Personally, having played other characters that are archetypical in what they do, I find that playing the Beastlord is a refreshing change. I concur we have no &quot;one thing&quot; that shines above any other class, but it is our versatility that really makes playing a BST fun. It's nice to be able to play a tank, cleric (for pet), shaman, or mage to some degree without feeling pigeon-holed into a specific role. That's what made me abandon my druid (sit-med-heal-nuke-rinse-repeat) and my monk (pull-FD-pull-FD)<br>
<br>
Now, granted, that might not get me invited to too many Creator raids (well, until level 60 for Savagery/Spiritual Purity anyways), but for playing the game, it's a hoot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
